OL,3,C'Chopstick Sally' allows housebound
OL,4,Cauthor to feel more included in society
OL,6,FAn author who is housebound and
OL,7,Flargely bedbound has been using a
OL,8,Fminiature cardboard cutout version of
OL,9,Fherself on chopsticks as a way to
OL,10,F"feel more included" in society.
OL,12,FSally Doherty, who lives in Surrey,
OL,13,Fwas diagnosed with myalgic
OL,14,Fencephalomyelitis (ME) in May 2006
OL,15,Fafter falling ill in late 2005.
OL,17,F"I fell ill in my early twenties
OL,18,F(completely unexpectedly following a
OL,19,Fsimple cold) in October 2005, and over
OL,20,Fthe space of a week my life ground to
OL,21,Fa halt," she told the PA news agency.
